Some reviewers praise its flashy visuals and fun gameplay, while others criticize its shallowness and dullness. Forbes highlights the game's immersive story and world-building, while The Verge focuses on its repetitive and uninspired combat. IGN examines the game's technical aspects, praising its graphics and performance. TheGamer emphasizes the game's protagonist, Eve, and her compelling character development. Press Start Australia provides information on the game's availability and pricing in Australia. Gadgetguy.com.au initially had a negative opinion but later revised their assessment, citing the game's enjoyable aspects despite its flaws. Gamesradar acknowledges the game's issues but ultimately finds it enjoyable. Kotaku praises the game's visuals and combat but notes its repetitive gameplay. Checkpoint concludes that "Stellar Blade" offers a solid action-RPG experience with an engaging protagonist and a well-crafted world.
